@4KarenStocks It took a lot of planning but we recently moved our hands-on classroom training in #Rstats to the #virtual world with the help of #RStudioPro - basically like the Google Docs of R. You can code collaboratively with others in real time!

Unable to get out for #FieldworkFriday but interested in physical #samples? Invertebrates, soil, and small mammal samples and specimens from many regions, including #Alaska, are all available through the @NEON_sci Biorepository. https://t.co/oBCFJu87Gc https://t.co/JmEHUYuxv1

Get credit for your #Arctic #data! Register journal articles that use your data. We recently developed a feature that allows users to directly link journal articles to any @arcticdatactr dataset. Read more:  https://t.co/1k4zC6J1dc #FAIRdata #OpenData https://t.co/6f1srNYTdL

#NewPaper alert from @GRocherRos: carbon chemistry suggests that metabolic activity regulates CO2 production in #Arctic streams; future emissions may depend on stream denizens respond to #climatechange. #WildWednesday Paper: https://t.co/iQAUbBbCIq Data: https://t.co/l93drN5gHt https://t.co/v8oCpccUZj
I imagine we'll see some interesting results out of this! #openresearch #survey #virtualconferences https://t.co/jN7UHEwgIt
And if you have any questions about #opendata #datascience #dataviz, ask away! #datahelpdesk https://t.co/de9YBCUiM7

Plus PLUS (@sjeanetteclark weighing in), most research is built upon larger and more complex data than a single file would support. Ideally, the entire research workflow would be preserved which is going to be much more than supplemental files can handle. #datahelpdesk #FAIRdata

From our PI @metamattj: supplements are not discoverable, generally lack metadata, and are often structured as PDFs rather than appropriately as data files. Plus, journals have historically not maintained them well, so they disappear over time. The idea is to preserve AND reuse. https://t.co/eyTna4gtCx

#SpookyNewsTues - there's a #killer on the loose! Orcas (killer whales) have been found to prey on bowhead whales in the #Arctic - read more about the first multi-year study on non-harvest related mortalities of bowhead whales in this #newpaper. https://t.co/yDsRArEpuo https://t.co/IcoKqBVbNH
